-- Australian Equities: ANZ Bank, BHP Billiton, Rio, Orica, Santos
-- B y   J a c o b   G r e b e r
-- 2012-01-02T23:32:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/australian-equities-anz-bank-bhp-billiton-rio-orica-santos.html
Australia ’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index (AS51)  rose
1.1 percent to 4,100 at 10:25 a.m. in Sydney.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  Australia & New Zealand Banking Group Ltd. (ANZ)  
advanced 1.4 percent to A$20.82 in Sydney. The lender won its
biggest share of Australia’s bond underwriting market on record
after expanding in  Asia  and the nation’s banks captured the top
four slots for the first time since 2007.  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)   rose 1.6 percent to A$34.98. The
world’s biggest mining company gained after the London Metal
Exchange Index of six metals advanced 2.1 percent on Dec. 30.
 Rio Tinto Group (RIO)   climbed 1.6 percent to A$61.26.  Orica Ltd. (ORI)   gained 0.4 percent to A$24.33. The
world’s largest industrial explosives maker will restart an
ammonia plant in Australia today after it was shut by chemical
leaks.  Santos Ltd. (STO)   advanced 0.8 percent to A$12.34. The
Australian energy company gained after crude oil for February
delivery rose as much as 1.7 percent, to $100.51 a barrel in
electronic trading on the  New York Mercantile Exchange  as of
10:04 a.m. Sydney time.  Woodside Petroleum Ltd. (WPL)  gained 0.9
percent to A$30.98.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jacob Greber in Sydney at 
